## 3) Concepts & Definitions

### 3.1 Coverage Map
Per-property, per-category classification of what the homeowner already does:
- **SELF** — “I do it myself”
- **PROVIDER** — “I have someone”
- **NONE** — “Not handled / I need this”
- **NA** — “Not applicable (home doesn’t have this)”
Optional: **Switch intent** when they select PROVIDER:
- **OPEN_NOW / OPEN_LATER / NOT_OPEN**

### 3.2 Property Sizing Signals
Fast, range-based fields (not exact numbers):
- **Home sqft range**
- **Yard size tier**
- **Windows tier**
- **Stories tier** (only if you choose; highly relevant for gutters/windows)
- **Pool flag** (can be derived from coverage map NA vs not, but can also be explicit)

### 3.3 Personalization Signals
A normalized payload derived from coverage map + sizing, used by:
- Add-on suggestion engine (later 3C, but signals must exist now)
- Level default selection (immediate integration with 3A)

