## 6) Data Model (Supabase)

> The exact naming can match your existing schema. The structure below is the intent.

### 6.1 New tables

#### `property_coverage`
One row per property per category.
- `id` uuid pk
- `property_id` uuid fk
- `category_key` text (enum-like)
- `coverage_status` text (`SELF|PROVIDER|NONE|NA`)
- `switch_intent` text null (`OPEN_NOW|OPEN_LATER|NOT_OPEN`)
- `updated_at` timestamptz
- Unique: `(property_id, category_key)`

#### `property_signals`
One row per property.
- `property_id` uuid pk
- `home_sqft_tier` text null
- `yard_tier` text null
- `windows_tier` text null
- `stories_tier` text null
- `signals_version` int default 1
- `updated_at` timestamptz

#### `personalization_events` (optional but useful)
Append-only events for analytics / tuning.
- `id` uuid pk
- `property_id`
- `event_type` text (coverage_updated, sizing_updated)
- `payload` jsonb
- `created_at`

### 6.2 Existing table changes (likely)
- Ensure `properties` has `property_id` stable key used everywhere.
- Routine items should already have SKU id and Level id from 3A; if not, add:
  - `routine_items.sku_level_id`

